 <purpose>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of a method by which an activity may be performed.
   <note>
     The Activity_method module provides a foundation for 
     more detailed and specific specifications of how particular activities are to be performed. 
   </note>
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
   <li>identification and description of an activity method.</li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
   <li>
     description of activities;
     <note>
     This requirement is dealt with by the <module_ref linkend="activity:1_scope">
     activity
   </module_ref> module.
 </note>
   </li>
	 <li>assignment of an activity method to an activity that shall use it;</li>
	 <li>association of an activity method to a work request to represent a way to resolve the request.</li>
 </outscope>

